{"art": [], "author": [{"email_address": "wgstexas@gmail.com", "first_name": "W. Gardner", "id": 122, "last_name": "Selby", "name_slug": "w-gardner-selby", "on_staff_page": 84, "phone": "", "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 3, "publication_name": "Austin American-Statesman", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/3/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/122/", "title": "Former PolitiFact Texas editor", "twitter": ""}], "canonical_url": "/texas/statements/2010/jul/05/david-barton/gops-david-barton-says-republican-legislator-did-a/", "edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Texas", "edition": "Texas", "edition_slug": "texas", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 2, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The Texas Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/2/"}, "editor": [], "facebook_headline": null, "id": 2004, "in_future": false, "is_pundit": false, "make_public": true, "preview": true, "researcher": [{"email_address": "wgstexas@gmail.com", "first_name": "W. Gardner", "id": 122, "last_name": "Selby", "name_slug": "w-gardner-selby", "on_staff_page": 84, "phone": "", "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 3, "publication_name": "Austin American-Statesman", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/3/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/122/", "title": "Former PolitiFact Texas editor", "twitter": ""}], "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statement/2004/", "ruling": {"adkey": "Truth-O-Meter", "advalue": "Mostly True", "id": 2, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementruling/2/", "ruling": "Mostly True", "ruling_graphic": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/rulings/tom-mostlytrue.png", "ruling_slug": "mostly-true"}, "ruling_comments": "<p>In an open letter distributed June 12 to delegates to the Republican Party of Texas convention, former party vice chairman David Barton of Aledo depicts Texas House Speaker Joe Straus, a San Antonio Republican, as part of a Democrat-friendly cabal that needs to be shaped up or shipped out.</p>\r\n<p>Barton&rsquo;s letter excoriates instances of Republican House members pitching in to help Democrats win re-election. An excerpt: &ldquo;Straus Republican lieutenant Jim Keffer did mail pieces for Democrat Mark Strama to help him defeat his Republican opponent.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Keffer hails from Eastland, some 160 miles northwest of Austin, whose legislative delegation includes Strama. Did a rural Republican really back the re-election of an urban colleague from the other party?</p>\r\n<p>When we asked for elaboration, Barton shared copies of what he said were two political leaflets from a Strama re-election campaign.</p>\r\n<p>One of the documents includes pro-Strama quotations from former State Comptroller John Sharp, a Democrat; the Democrat-leaning Austin Chronicle; a resident of Strama&rsquo;s district and Keffer, who&rsquo;s quoted saying: &ldquo;Mark Strama serves his district, not any one political party.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>In the other document, Sharp and Keffer are also featured. Keffer is quoted saying Strama &ldquo;worked with Republicans to cut property taxes and keep our public schools open. We don't always agree on every issue, but we agree on the need to put the interests of Texas ahead of partisan politics.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Responding to our query, Keffer confirmed he&rsquo;d given Strama a hand, saying: &ldquo;Whether you&rsquo;ve got an R or a D behind your name doesn&rsquo;t mean you are most qualified.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Finally, we contacted Strama, who told us by e-mail that Keffer, who had authored school funding legislaton that Strama co-sponsored, &ldquo;didn&rsquo;t &lsquo;do&rsquo; mail pieces in the sense of paying for them,&rdquo; but agreed to be quoted in a mailer &ldquo;funded by my campaign about my bipartisan approach to the school finance bill.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Though Strama paid for the campaign materials, Keffer willingly helped out his Democratic colleague. Barton&rsquo;s statement checks out as Mostly True.</p>", "ruling_comments_date": "2010-07-02T19:54:57.267534", "ruling_date": "2010-07-05T12:00:00", "ruling_headline": "GOP's David Barton says Republican legislator did ads for Democrat Mark Strama of Austin", "ruling_headline_slug": "gops-david-barton-says-republican-legislator-did-a", "ruling_link_text": "Keffer admires Austin Democrat, though didn't do mailings", "ruling_state": null, "source_documents": null, "sources": "<p><a href=\"http://alt.coxnewsweb.com/statesman/politifact/06192010_davidbartonresponse.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline;\">E-mail</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> (excerpted), Joe  Barton, GOP activist, Aledo, Texas, June 19, 2010</span><br /><br /><a href=\"http://alt.coxnewsweb.com/statesman/politifact/06222010_markstramaresponse.pdf,\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline;\">E-mail</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> (excerpted), State  Rep. Mark Strama, Austin, June 22, 2010</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Interview, Rep. Jim  Keffer, Eastland, June 22, 2010</span><br /><br /><a href=\"http://www.symsys.com/cgi-bin/citydist?block1=Austin%2C+TX&amp;block2=Eastland%2C+TX&amp;ok=OKAY\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline;\">Mileage  Calculator Results,</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> Austin, Texas to Eastland, Texas, accessed June 28, 2010</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Open letter, David  Barton, Aledo,</span><a href=\"http://alt.coxnewsweb.com/statesman/politifact/%2006122010_davidbartonletter.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline;\"> &ldquo;Conservative  Growth in Texas: Danger from Within,&rdquo;</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> distributed at Republican Party of  Texas state convention, Dallas, June 12, 2010</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Mark Strama campaign,  leaflets,</span><a href=\"http://alt.coxnewsweb.com/statesman/politifact/10202006_bipartisanstrama.pdf%20\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline;\"> &ldquo;Bipartisan  support for Mark Strama&rdquo;</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> and</span><a href=\"http://alt.coxnewsweb.com/statesman/politifact/10202006_stramaworktgther.pdf%20\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline;\"> &ldquo;Working  together,&rdquo;</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> copies provided by David Barton</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"></span></p>", "speaker": {"adkey": null, "advalue": null, "barely_true_count": 1, "current_job": "President, Wallbuilders", "false_count": 0, "first_name": "David", "half_true_count": 1, "home_state": "Texas", "id": 498, "last_name": "Barton", "mostly_true_count": 2, "name_slug": "david-barton", "pants_count": 0, "party": {"id": 3, "party": "Republican", "party_slug": "republican", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/party/3/"}, "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/mugs/davidbartonap.jpg", "primary_edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Texas", "edition": "Texas", "edition_slug": "texas", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 2, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The Texas Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/2/"}, "promise_meter_cutout": null, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/person/498/", "total_count": 4, "true_count": 0, "website": "http://www.wallbuilders.com/"}, "statement": "<p>Says state Rep. Jim Keffer, a GOP lieutenant to House Speaker Joe Straus, \"did mail pieces for Democrat  Mark Strama to help him defeat\" a Republican.</p>", "